<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://courses.ncssm.edu/GALLERY/collections/toys/html/exhibit10.htm" class="external text" title="http://courses.ncssm.edu/GALLERY/collections/toys/html/exhibit10.htm" rel="nofollow">"Zoetrope"</a>. <i>Laura Hayes and John Howard Wileman Exhibit of Optical Toys</i>. The North Carolina School of Science and Mathematics. 2005<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://courses.ncssm.edu/GALLERY/collections/toys/html/exhibit10.htm" class="external free" title="http://courses.ncssm.edu/GALLERY/collections/toys/html/exhibit10.htm" rel="nofollow">http://courses.ncssm.edu/GALLERY/collections/toys/html/exhibit10.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-05-13</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Zoetrope&amp;rft.atitle=Laura+Hayes+and+John+Howard+Wileman+Exhibit+of+Optical+Toys&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.pub=The+North+Carolina+School+of+Science+and+Mathematics&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcourses.ncssm.edu%2FGALLERY%2Fcollections%2Ftoys%2Fhtml%2Fexhibit10.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Zoetrope"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.nbc4.com/news/8457121/detail.html" class="external text" title="http://www.nbc4.com/news/8457121/detail.html" rel="nofollow"><em>Metro begins testing new tunnel ads</em></a>, NBC4, April 4, 2006</li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> www.motionflow.eu</li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.engadgethd.com/2008/12/21/sony-sets-guinness-world-record-with-bravia-drome" class="external free" title="http://www.engadgethd.com/2008/12/21/sony-sets-guinness-world-record-with-bravia-drome" rel="nofollow">http://www.engadgethd.com/2008/12/21/sony-sets-guinness-world-record-with-bravia-drome</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news">"<a href="http://www.popsci.com.au/entertainment-amp-gaming/article/2009-02/sony-creates-world%E2%80%99s-largest-zoetrope" class="external text" title="http://www.popsci.com.au/entertainment-amp-gaming/article/2009-02/sony-creates-world%E2%80%99s-largest-zoetrope" rel="nofollow">Sony Creates World’s Largest Zoetrope</a>". <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=PopSci.com.au&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="PopSci.com.au (page does not exist)">PopSci.com.au</a></i>. <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2009-02-18"><a href="/wiki/2009" title="2009">2009</a>-<a href="/wiki/February_18" title="February 18">02-18</a></span><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.popsci.com.au/entertainment-amp-gaming/article/2009-02/sony-creates-world%E2%80%99s-largest-zoetrope" class="external free" title="http://www.popsci.com.au/entertainment-amp-gaming/article/2009-02/sony-creates-world%E2%80%99s-largest-zoetrope" rel="nofollow">http://www.popsci.com.au/entertainment-amp-gaming/article/2009-02/sony-creates-world%E2%80%99s-largest-zoetrope</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2009-02-18</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Sony+Creates+World%E2%80%99s+Largest+Zoetrope&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BPopSci.com.au%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=%5B%5B2009-02-18%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.popsci.com.au%2Fentertainment-amp-gaming%2Farticle%2F2009-02%2Fsony-creates-world%25E2%2580%2599s-largest-zoetrope&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Zoetrope"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ol>
<p>Culver City, California, current home of Sony Studios (originally MGM)has several zoetropes placed throughout the main street area.</p>
